Malaysians Told to Stay Indoors Amid Air Pollution, Bernama Says

-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 
2011-05-13T05:40:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/malaysians-told-to-stay-indoors-amid-air-pollution-bernama-says.html
Malaysia has asked the public to
reduce outdoor activities after the  air quality  in several areas
in the country worsened, state news service Bernama reported,
citing a statement from the health ministry.  Towns including Port Klang, Bukit Rambai, Melaka and Port
Dickson have recorded high readings on the  air pollutant index ,
the report said. The public is advised to wear masks outdoors
and drink plenty of water, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chong Pooi Koon in Kuala Lumpur at 
 pchong17@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
